\pard\plain \tx1123\tx1685\tx2246\tx2794\tx3355\tx3917\tx4478\tx5040\tx5602\tx6163\tx6725\fi720\ri-720\sl288\slmult1\ql\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The next day they came to a natron flat two miles long and as many wide. Seb broke off small chunks of the white stuff and rubbed it on her gums. She claimed it could make missing teeth grow back. Mandri knew natron for its use in pigment. A tiny amount mixed in with quartz sand and copper ore made a blue called Canzr Blue. The most vibrant hues came from Canzr, where more than a hundred slaves spent their days sorting the quartz sand for impurities, grain by grain, with tweezers. Only the cleanest, purest crystals were worthy of inclusion.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Moteah found this fact distasteful instead of impressive. Mandri was quick to agree, as it was brutal work. Those slaves were forced to sort the grains at all hours, even at night. Many went blind from staring too hard in the dimness of candlelight.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 No one else much cared about any of this. Elrahet was especially indifferent\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 a detail that he\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d noticed now that he was paying particular attention to her moods.}}